# KiCad
# For PCBs designed using KiCad: https://kicad-pcb.org

# Backup files
#
# KiCad makes various backup files (e.g. `file.kicad_pcb-bak`, `file.sch-bak`,
# `~file.kicad_pcb`, etc). These are local history and should not be committed
# to the repository.
#
# Older KiCad versions:
*~
*.bck
*.bak
*.000

# KiCad 6+ backup files:
*-bak.kicad_*

# KiCad 6+ lock files
#
# Lock files are used to prevent concurrent edits and should not be committed.
*.lck

# Cache files
#
# The footprint info cache file can be safely ignored. It is automatically
# re-generated by KiCad as needed.
fp-info-cache

# Local project settings
#
# The .kicad_prl file contains display settings (zoom, scrollbar positions,
# etc) specific to the local user.
*.kicad_prl

# Netlist files
#
# Netlists are generated from the schematic and used to import/update the PCB.
# They are not necessary for version control as the schematic file is the
# source of truth.
*.net

# Autorouter files
#
# Files generated by external autorouters can be ignored.
*.dsn
*.ses

# Exported BOM files
#
# BOM files are generated from the schematic and should not be committed. The
# script/tool used to generate the BOM should be committed instead.
*.xml
*.csv
*.tsv
*.json
*.html

# Generated manufacturing files
#
# KiCad does not use a fixed directory structure for output files, so it is
# up to the user to configure the output location. If the output is kept within
# the project directory, it should be ignored.
#
# A common practice is to output to a "build" or "gerbers" directory.
/build/
/gerbers/
/production_files/

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.log
*.raw
# Used by the SVG2Shenzhen extension
.svg2shenzhen-cache/
.history/